<title>SRI LANKA: Sri Lanka, Thailand discuss airline for Buddhists.</title>
<headline>Sri Lanka, Thailand discuss airline for Buddhists.</headline>
<dateline>COLOMBO 1997-07-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>Sri Lanka and Thailand have discussed the possibility of launching a private airline to meet rising pilgrim traffic between Buddhist countries, a Sri Lanka Foreign Ministry statement said on Tuesday.</p>
<p>It said Sri Lankan Foreign Minister Lakshman Kadirgamar met his Thai counterpart Prachaub Chaiyasarn in Bangkok last week and discussed the need to promote Buddhist pilgrim traffic to Sri Lanka, Thailand, Burma and India.</p>
<p>The proposed airline would help pilgrims from other Buddhist nations like Japan, China, Cambodia, Laos, South Korea, Japan and Mongolia to visit religious centers in the four countries, the statement said.</p>
<p>It gave no other details.</p>
